title: NC Center for Geographic Info and Analysis (NCCGIA), Water Distribution Systems - Type B Service Areas, N Carolina, 1997
name: NC Center for Geographic Info and Analysis (NCCGIA), Water Distribution Systems - Type B Service Areas, N Carolina, 1997
description:
The NCREDC in conjunction with Hobbs, Upchurch & Associates developed the digital ``B' Water System as mapped by individual system owners as required by contract. The data collected will facilitate planning, siting and impact analysis in the 70 individual counties of North Carolina. This file enables the user to make various county-level determinations when used in conjunction with other data layers. This data contains information on ``B' water systems as defined by NCREDC, system ID, system name, population served, owner's name and telephone number. Other coverages exist with water lines and other appurtenances.

This data was created to assist governmental agencies and others in making resource management decisions through use of a Geographic Information System (GIS).
